                            <comment id="12792589" author="rding" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2009 19:13:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Without -M option Pig converts paths to their absolute locations before passing them to the loaders/storers. With -M option, Pig passes the paths &quot;as is&quot; to the loaders/storers. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This distinction seems to be obsolete. The fix will be to convert paths to their absolute locations in both cases.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
